arChildNodes.szComment: Unfazed with alcohol, Nairne confirms she took the sign as a “trophy” for her dear friend Tavish.
Nairne somberly notes that goatmen killed Tavish where she sits only days prior.
In response, she thought it right to steal the Goose sign and bring it to the spot of his death for a final drink together.
Nairne mentions Tavish’s incomplete “List of Last Deeds."
Nairne requests the player’s assistance in finishing the list. She hopes completing the list will bring Tavish peace and knowledge he'll be remembered.
Nairne shares her desire to place the daggers (bearing Tavish’s cloth) at the locations on the list, marking them for Tavish—completing the “deed” for him.
